PELZER v. DALE CO. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 27, 1901.) No. 91. Appeal from the Circuit Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Richard N. Dyer, for appellant. Henry M. Brigham, for appellee.

Before WALLACE and LACOMBE, Circuit Judges. No opinion. Decree of circuit court (103 Fed. 494) affirmed, with costs, on opinion below.
